						               													<description>Take turns building the barricade to keep the zombies at bay!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In this abstract dexterity game, you take on the roles of a group of survivors trying to escape a zombie apocalypse.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;To keep the zombies at bay, each player needs to help build up the barricade with random pieces carefully stacked on each other. However, at times a player must also remove a part of the barricade to salvage parts for fixing the escape car.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The die adds luck to the situation which can land a player in the dreaded &amp;quot;blind stacking&amp;quot; event where they must depend on the other players' directions/clues to blindly place a barricade piece without toppling it all over. It only takes a handful of mistakes for the players to lose so keep a steady hand and focused mind. The barricade must not fall!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;A game turn is comprised of 3 phases:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     Barricade Phase - roll the red D6 Action die &amp;amp; consult the Action table (add zombies or add to the barricade)&amp;#10;     Car Phase - roll the red D6 Action die &amp;amp; consult the Action table (add zombies or remove from the barricade)&amp;#10;     End Phase - zombie check &amp;amp; increase the black D8 Hour die&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Players loose if there are 10 zombies at the barricade.&amp;#10;Players win if the D8 Hour die value exceeds 8.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
